# Migration Phase 2b: Specification Review

## Purpose & Scope

This rule defines the comprehensive review process that validates technical specifications for completeness, accuracy, and implementation readiness before proceeding to migration planning. Phase 2b is a critical quality gate that prevents downstream issues through multi-stakeholder validation, ensures business logic preservation, and confirms development team readiness for implementation.

**Applies to**:
- C++ to C# migration projects with completed Phase 2 technical specifications
- Multi-stakeholder review and validation process
- Quality gate validation before Phase 3 migration planning
- Formal sign-off and approval process

**Does not apply to**:
- Initial specification creation (covered by Phase 2 rule)
- Data collection activities (covered by Phase 1 rule)
- Migration planning or implementation (covered by Phase 3 rule)
- Day-to-day development code reviews
- Post-implementation validation testing

## Inputs (Contract)

- Complete Phase 2 technical specification suite with all required documents
- Phase 1 data collection findings for cross-reference validation
- Phase 2 cross-reference index linking all specifications
- Stakeholder review team assembled (technical, business, implementation, integration, performance, QA)
- Review schedule with allocated time for each stakeholder category
- Issue tracking system for documenting review findings
- Phase 2 quality gate report indicating specification creation completion

## Outputs (Contract)

- Comprehensive review findings report with all issues categorized (Critical, Major, Minor)
- Technical accuracy sign-off from senior developers and architects
- Business accuracy confirmation from domain experts and business analysts
- Implementation readiness assessment from development team leads
- Integration compatibility validation from integration architects
- Performance requirements approval from performance engineers
- Documentation quality approval from QA specialists
- Issue resolution log showing all findings addressed or accepted
- Updated specifications incorporating all approved changes from review
- Formal stakeholder sign-offs from all review categories
- Phase 2b quality gate report with pass/fail status
- Risk register identifying risks with mitigation strategies for Phase 3

## Review Strategy

### **Multi-Stakeholder Review Process**
- **Technical Review**: Verify completeness and technical accuracy
- **Business Review**: Validate business rules and requirements
- **Implementation Review**: Assess implementation readiness
- **Integration Review**: Verify external system compatibility
- **Performance Review**: Validate performance requirements
- **Quality Assurance Review**: Ensure documentation standards compliance

### **Review Phases**
- **Phase 1**: Individual stakeholder reviews (parallel execution)
- **Phase 2**: Cross-functional review sessions (collaborative validation)
- **Phase 3**: Issue resolution and specification updates
- **Phase 4**: Final approval and sign-off

## Technical Review Process

### **Completeness Assessment**
- **Objective**: Verify all current system functionality is captured
- **Reviewers**: Senior developers, system architects, C++ specialists
- **Activities**:
  - Cross-reference specifications against Phase 1 findings
  - Identify any missing business logic or algorithms
  - Verify all integration points are documented
  - Confirm all data structures and relationships are captured
- **Success Criteria**: 100% coverage of current system capabilities

### **Accuracy Validation**
- **Objective**: Ensure specifications reflect actual system behavior
- **Activities**:
  - Validate business rules against source code analysis
  - Verify enumeration values and algorithm specifications
  - Confirm entity relationships match actual implementation
  - Test specification clarity with implementation scenarios
- **Deliverables**: Technical accuracy sign-off with any required corrections

### **Implementation Readiness Assessment**
- **Objective**: Verify development team can implement from specifications
- **Reviewers**: Lead developers, domain specialists
- **Activities**:
  - Review specifications for implementation clarity
  - Identify ambiguous or incomplete requirements
  - Assess complexity and technical risks
  - Validate migration considerations are complete
- **Success Criteria**: Development team confidence in implementation readiness

## Business Review Process

### **Business Rule Validation**
- **Objective**: Confirm all business rules are accurately captured
- **Reviewers**: Business analysts, subject matter experts, process owners
- **Activities**:
  - Validate business logic specifications against real-world processes
  - Confirm calculation algorithms match business requirements
  - Verify condition evaluation logic reflects business intent
  - Review integration requirements for business accuracy
- **Deliverables**: Business accuracy confirmation with stakeholder sign-off

### **Requirements Completeness Check**
- **Objective**: Ensure all business requirements are addressed
- **Activities**:
  - Cross-reference specifications against original business requirements
  - Identify any missing functionality or edge cases
  - Validate performance requirements meet business needs
  - Confirm integration requirements support business processes
- **Success Criteria**: Complete business requirements coverage

### **User Impact Assessment**
- **Objective**: Evaluate impact on business users and processes
- **Activities**:
  - Review specifications for user experience implications
  - Assess impact on existing business workflows
  - Validate data migration requirements
  - Confirm reporting and analytics capabilities
- **Deliverables**: User impact analysis and mitigation strategies

## Implementation Review Process

### **Development Team Assessment**
- **Objective**: Validate specifications support effective development
- **Reviewers**: Development team leads, senior developers
- **Activities**:
  - Review specifications for development clarity and completeness
  - Assess technical complexity and implementation risks
  - Validate technology choices and architectural decisions
  - Confirm testing strategies are feasible
- **Success Criteria**: Development team commitment to deliver from specifications

### **Architecture Review**
- **Objective**: Ensure specifications support target architecture
- **Reviewers**: Solution architects, enterprise architects
- **Activities**:
  - Validate specifications align with architectural standards
  - Review integration patterns and service boundaries
  - Assess scalability and performance implications
  - Confirm security and compliance requirements
- **Deliverables**: Architecture approval with any required modifications

### **Technology Compatibility Check**
- **Objective**: Verify specifications are compatible with target technology stack
- **Activities**:
  - Review C# implementation considerations
  - Validate database and persistence requirements
  - Assess integration technology compatibility
  - Confirm monitoring and operational requirements
- **Success Criteria**: Technology stack compatibility confirmed

## Integration Review Process

### **External System Impact Assessment**
- **Objective**: Validate impact on external systems and interfaces
- **Reviewers**: Integration architects, external system representatives
- **Activities**:
  - Review all external integration specifications
  - Validate API contracts and data formats
  - Assess backward compatibility requirements
  - Confirm migration timing coordination with external systems
- **Deliverables**: Integration impact analysis and coordination plan

### **Data Migration Review**
- **Objective**: Ensure data migration requirements are complete
- **Activities**:
  - Review data structure mappings and transformation requirements
  - Validate data integrity and validation requirements
  - Assess data migration timeline and dependencies
  - Confirm rollback and recovery procedures
- **Success Criteria**: Data migration strategy approved by all stakeholders

## Performance Review Process

### **Performance Requirements Validation**
- **Objective**: Confirm performance requirements are realistic and complete
- **Reviewers**: Performance engineers, system architects
- **Activities**:
  - Review performance benchmarks and targets
  - Validate caching and optimization strategies
  - Assess scalability requirements and growth projections
  - Confirm monitoring and alerting requirements
- **Deliverables**: Performance requirements approval with success criteria

### **Capacity Planning Review**
- **Objective**: Ensure infrastructure requirements are adequate
- **Activities**:
  - Review resource requirements and capacity needs
  - Validate infrastructure scaling capabilities
  - Assess disaster recovery and business continuity requirements
  - Confirm operational monitoring and support capabilities
- **Success Criteria**: Infrastructure readiness confirmed

## Quality Assurance Review

### **Documentation Standards Compliance**
- **Objective**: Ensure specifications meet quality and maintainability standards
- **Reviewers**: Technical writers, quality assurance specialists
- **Activities**:
  - Review documentation structure and organization
  - Validate cross-references and navigation
  - Assess completeness and clarity of content
  - Confirm compliance with documentation standards
- **Deliverables**: Documentation quality approval

### **Traceability Validation**
- **Objective**: Verify specifications are traceable to source requirements
- **Activities**:
  - Confirm all Phase 1 findings are addressed in specifications
  - Validate business requirements traceability
  - Review source code references and accuracy
  - Assess completeness of migration considerations
- **Success Criteria**: Complete traceability established

